      "text": "- Do not write comments that simply restate what the code is doing. Your code should be self-documenting through thoughtful name choices and types, so such comments would be redundant, wasting the user's time and tokens.\\n- Only use comments to explain \\\"why\\\" the code is necessary, or explain context or connections to other pieces of the code that is not colocated with the comment\\n\\n# Working with Plans\\n\\nWhen working on implementing a plan from a `plans/` file:\\n- Check off completed items by changing `- [ ]` to `- [x]` as you complete each step\\n- Update the plan file regularly to track your progress\\n- This helps both you and the user see what's been accomplished and what remains\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": \"Please run the command: echo test\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"tools\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"function\",\n          \"function\": {\n            \"name\": \"bash_command\",\n            \"description\": \"Run a command in a bash shell.\\nYou will get the stdout and stderr of the command, as well as the exit code.\\nFor example, you can run `ls`, `echo 'Hello, World!'`, or `git status`.\\nThe command will time out after 1 min.\\nYou should not run commands that require user input, such as `git commit` without `-m` or `ssh`.\\nYou should not run commands that do not halt, such as `docker compose up` without `-d`, `tail -f` or `watch`.\\n\",\n            \"parameters\": {\n              \"type\": \"object\",\n              \"properties\": {\n                \"command\": {\n                  \"type\": \"string\",\n                  \"description\": \"The command to run in the terminal\"\n                }\n              },\n              \"required\": [\"command\"],\n              \"additionalProperties\": false\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"status\": 200,\n    \"response\": \"data: {\\\"choices\\\":[{\\\"index\\\":0,\\\"delta\\\":{\\\"content\\\":\\\"I\\\",\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\"}}],\\\"created\\\":1752562345,\\\"id\\\":\\\"42f2217f-4e05-4dd5-8450-6102108ae263\\\",\\\"model\\\":\\\"",
      "contextualizedText": "// node/test/recordings/bash-command-tool-use.json \u003e [1]\n\n- Do not write comments that simply restate what the code is doing. Your code should be self-documenting through thoughtful name choices and types, so such comments would be redundant, wasting the user's time and tokens.\\n- Only use comments to explain \\\"why\\\" the code is necessary, or explain context or connections to other pieces of the code that is not colocated with the comment\\n\\n# Working with Plans\\n\\nWhen working on implementing a plan from a `plans/` file:\\n- Check off completed items by changing `- [ ]` to `- [x]` as you complete each step\\n- Update the plan file regularly to track your progress\\n- This helps both you and the user see what's been accomplished and what remains\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"user\",\n          \"content\": \"Please run the command: echo test\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"tools\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"function\",\n          \"function\": {\n            \"name\": \"bash_command\",\n            \"description\": \"Run a command in a bash shell.\\nYou will get the stdout and stderr of the command, as well as the exit code.\\nFor example, you can run `ls`, `echo 'Hello, World!'`, or `git status`.\\nThe command will time out after 1 min.\\nYou should not run commands that require user input, such as `git commit` without `-m` or `ssh`.\\nYou should not run commands that do not halt, such as `docker compose up` without `-d`, `tail -f` or `watch`.\\n\",\n            \"parameters\": {\n              \"type\": \"object\",\n              \"properties\": {\n                \"command\": {\n                  \"type\": \"string\",\n                  \"description\": \"The command to run in the terminal\"\n                }\n              },\n              \"required\": [\"command\"],\n              \"additionalProperties\": false\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"status\": 20